<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1482,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1519,1545]" pageId="1" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antenna 1 elongate, as long as antenna 2 peduncle. Mandible left lacinia mobilis 4 dentate. Maxilliped palp article 2 without medial lobe; article 4 small, but distinct. Gnathopod 1 subchelate; posterior margins of merus, carpus and propodus each with lobe covered in palmate setae. Gnathopod 2 subchelate in male, mitten-shaped in female. Pereopods 7 sexually dimorphic. Pleopods well developed. Uropods 1â€“2 outer ramus without robust setae. Uropod 3 ramus shorter than peduncle. Telson entire or apically incised, with 2 to 6 apical setae.
</paragraph>
